<ce:para>A general super-structure is proposed for the design of a wastewater networks for removing five types of contaminants (suspended solids, heavy metals, inorganic salts, organic contaminants unsuitable for biological treatment and organic contaminants suitable for biological treatment) using until 13 types of Best Available Technologies (BAT) technologies. The removal of the contaminants follows a specified sequence to avoid reducing the efficiency in the downstream technologies. The application of this superstructure, which is modeled as an MINLP, is illustrated for the design of a wastewater network for a metal finishing industry. © 2011 Elsevier B.V.</ce:para>
